<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="574" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1685,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1793,1818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to the Chinese 
<taxonomicName authority="Kononenko, 1997" authorityName="Kononenko" authorityYear="1997" box="[892,1255,1793,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimalis">
<emphasis box="[892,1040,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">H. minimalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1051,1255,1793,1818]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" refId="ref7616" refString="Kononenko, V. S. (1997) A revision of the Hoplodrina implacata species complex (Noctuidae, Amphipyrinae), with descriptions of three new species from China. Japan Heterocerists Journal, 193, 291 - 297." type="journal article">Kononenko, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1274,1350,1793,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[246,1325,564,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[246,1343,564,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Habitus of species of Hoplodrina implacata group. 1. H. implacata (Wileman &amp; West, 1929), female, holotype, Taiwan (©The Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London); 2. Ditto, labels (©The Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London); 3, 6. H. implacata, male, Taiwan; 4. H. cienensis sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 5. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (TFRI); 7. H. obscura sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 8. Ditto, paratype, male, Taiwan (TFRI); 9. H. minimalis Kononenko, 1997, male, China (NSMT); 10. H. kononenkoi sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 11. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (TFRI); 12. H. euryptera Boursin, 1937, male, Japan (NSMT); 13. H. bunun sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (NMNS); 14. Ditto, male, paratype, Taiwan (NSMT); 15. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (NSMT). Scale bar= 10 mm. Photo by Shen-Horn Yen (1, 2); Shipher Wu (3–15)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457395/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1366,1395,1794,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–23" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1712,1735]" captionTargetBox="[293,1283,512,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[290,1296,481,1691]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16–23. The male genitalia of the genus Hoplodrina species. 16. H. implacata (Wileman &amp; West, 1929), Taiwan (NSMT); 17. H. cienensis sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (TFRI); 18. H. obscura sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (TFRI); 19. H. kononenkoi sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (TFRI); 20. H. bunun sp. nov., paratype, Taiwan (NMNS); 21. H. persequora Ronkay, Ronkay, Fu &amp; Wu, 2013, Taiwan (TFRI); 22. H. minimalis Kononenko, 1997, China (NSMT); 23. H. euryptera Boursin, 1937, Japan (NSMT). Photo by Shipher Wu." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457397/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">19</figureCitation>
) in external appearance and genitalia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu &amp; Owada" authorityYear="2018" box="[564,810,1829,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cienensis">
<emphasis box="[564,810,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">Hoplodrina cienensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished in male genitalia by the more protruded valval apex; the apical margin of juxta excurved rather than concave; the more protruded saccus apex; the less developed cornuti. In female genitalia, the new species differs from the congeneric species by the presence of large distolateral half part of sclerotization in corpus bursae and the elongate bursae copulatrix. In female genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu &amp; Owada" authorityYear="2018" box="[261,399,1974,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cienensis">
<emphasis box="[261,399,1974,1997]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">H. cienensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wileman &amp; West" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[548,695,1973,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="implacata">
<emphasis box="[548,695,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">H. implacata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[710,1000,1973,1998]" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" refId="ref7616" refString="Kononenko, V. S. (1997) A revision of the Hoplodrina implacata species complex (Noctuidae, Amphipyrinae), with descriptions of three new species from China. Japan Heterocerists Journal, 193, 291 - 297." type="journal article">Kononenko, 1997: fig. 11</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kononenko" authorityYear="1997" box="[1065,1210,1973,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hoplodrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimalis">
<emphasis box="[1065,1210,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="574">H. minimalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="574" refId="ref7616" refString="Kononenko, V. S. (1997) A revision of the Hoplodrina implacata species complex (Noctuidae, Amphipyrinae), with descriptions of three new species from China. Japan Heterocerists Journal, 193, 291 - 297." type="journal article">Kononenko, 1997: fig. 14</bibRefCitation>
) by the strong sclerotized bursa copulatrix and the absence of the band-like transversal signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="576" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[429,524,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–15" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1777,1800]" captionTargetBox="[246,1325,564,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[246,1343,564,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–15. Habitus of species of Hoplodrina implacata group. 1. H. implacata (Wileman &amp; West, 1929), female, holotype, Taiwan (©The Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London); 2. Ditto, labels (©The Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London); 3, 6. H. implacata, male, Taiwan; 4. H. cienensis sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 5. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (TFRI); 7. H. obscura sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 8. Ditto, paratype, male, Taiwan (TFRI); 9. H. minimalis Kononenko, 1997, male, China (NSMT); 10. H. kononenkoi sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (TFRI); 11. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (TFRI); 12. H. euryptera Boursin, 1937, male, Japan (NSMT); 13. H. bunun sp. nov., male, holotype, Taiwan (NMNS); 14. Ditto, male, paratype, Taiwan (NSMT); 15. Ditto, paratype, female, Taiwan (NSMT). Scale bar= 10 mm. Photo by Shen-Horn Yen (1, 2); Shipher Wu (3–15)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457395/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
)—Forewing length 
<quantity box="[754,874,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">
13 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[782,796,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="575">–</emphasis>
14 mm
</quantity>
in males (n= 3); 
<quantity box="[1063,1142,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="575" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
in female (n= 1). Antenna filiform in male, ciliate in female. Head and thorax covered with lotus root grey scales. Forewing ground color silvery grey. Forewing antemedial line black, irregular, medial part tinged with dark grey band, postmedial line black, serrate; orbicular stigma small, round, reniform stigma wide elliptic, both surrounding with greyish white; submarginal line greyish white, parallel with outer margin; cilia and region between submarginal line and outer margin lotus root grey; distal part of cilia pale ochreous. Hindwing pale ochreous-grey at basal half part than gradually darken as dark grey, discal spot dark grey, distinct; outer margin and cilia pale ochreous. Abdomen pale lotus root grey.
</paragraph>
